# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO RE-LOAD DATA AFTER UPDATING SOURCE FILES
#
# Prerequisites (one-time):
#   python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
#   pip install httpx python-dotenv openpyxl pymupdf
#   Copy .env with SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_KEY (service role)
#
# 1) Updated Search_Results.xlsx (new/changed ADs from FAA DRS)?
#    python scripts/load_ads.py
#    python scripts/populate_ad_model_mapping.py
#
# 2) Downloaded a new SDR text file from FAA?
#    python scripts/load_data.py data.txt
#
# 3) Added/changed a lookup PDF in data/lookup/?
#    No script needed — get_jasc_description.py reads them at
#    import time. Just make sure the PDF is in data/lookup/.
#
# Order matters: run load_ads.py BEFORE populate_ad_model_mapping.py
# All scripts are idempotent (safe to re-run).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
